Kim Jong Il Provides Field Guidance to Janggang County 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il gave on-the-spot guidance to the work in various fields of Janggang County. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The first leg of his guidance was the Janggang Mushroom Farm. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round the exterior and interior of the farm including a spore cultivation room and a mushroom growing house, he acquainted himself in detail with the construction of the farm and its production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Being informed that the family members of Kim Yong Jong, manager of the farm, have worked heart and soul to increase the mushroom production on the same farm, he highly appreciated their patriotic deed, saying that such people working hard for the prosperity of the country are true patriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What is most important for cultivating mushroom is to establish a strict system for providing spores, he said, setting forth tasks to be fulfilled by the farm. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The next leg of his guidance was the Janggang Foodstuff Factory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Going round the technologically updated production processes, he got familiar in detail with equipment and production there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  He called upon the officials and other working people in the field of the light industry to bring about a radical turn in its development through the dynamic light industrial revolution, bearing deep in mind the high honor and pride of working in the important domain to improve the standard of the people's living. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He gave field guidance to the Janggang Rabbit Breeding Stock Farm. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He went round the interior of the modernly built breeding stock farm and highly praised the feats of its employees. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He visited the family of Kim Chol Su, head of a work-team, who set an example in raising rabbits. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Saying that rabbit is a domestic animal ensuring high productivity, he stressed the need to raise rabbits in a big way to provide the people in the county with conditions for richer diet. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He commanded a bird's-eye view of Janggang township built as a socialist land of bliss. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He looked round a photo exhibition now under way in Jagang Province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seeing significant photos one by one, he recollected with deep emotion on the ten year-long history of hardships and the unforgettable officials and people of the province. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said with profound emotion that the workers and other people in the province are loyalists who took the lead in pulling through difficulties sharing the idea, intention, breath and destiny with the Party when the country was in the most difficult situation and the precious revolutionary comrades who gave him courage with staunch fighting spirit and matchless valor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No weapon can overpower the strength of the Korean people having such a great history as the "Arduous March," the forced march as a legacy, he said, expressing great expectation and conviction that the working people in the province would continue to successfully perform the role of vanguard in the gigantic struggle to build a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Pak To Chun, chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial Committee of the WPK, and Kim Ki Nam, secretary of the WPK Central Committee.

U.S., Source of Worldwide Economic Instability 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- The world economy is slumping into a serious disorder. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The growing alarm over the economic depression in the United States has caused stock price slumps worldwide and called forth voices of unrest and concern about an economic crisis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The main factor of this worldwide economic instability is generally traced to the sharp rise of the oil price and the crisis of housing market in the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But a close scrutiny reveals that the consequences of the reckless war policy and "anti-terrorism war" of the U.S. underlie it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Entering upon the 21st century, the U.S. has provoked three wars including the Afghanistan war and the proxy war in Lebanon, prompted by its "anti-terrorism war" strategy for maintaining its position as "the only super power" in the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Lebanese war ended with a woeful defeat of the U.S. and Israel and the wars in Afghanistan and Iraq, which had been started earlier, are sinking deeper into a hopeless bog. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bankruptcy of the "anti-terrorism war" means the close of the "U.S. age". So the U.S. is hurling a greater amount of fund into these wars and trying to find a way out of the serious financial crisis in the growth of export by the devaluation of the dollar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. administration has steadily cut the rate of interest by switching over from the dollar overvaluation policy to its devaluation policy over the last three years. The deficit recorded the lowest mark in the fiscal year of 2007 for recent five years. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Consequent upon this, the oil price in the world market broke the 100 dollar mark per barrel, far beyond its real value, in January this year. This posed a serious threat not only to the oil consumer states but also to the oil producer states. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The dollar devaluation policy of the U.S. administration to fend off the catastrophic effect of the "anti-terrorism war" on the domestic economy is the fundamental cause of the jumping oil price, which cannot be put on a par with the speculation on the oil market and "imbalance between demand and supply".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The crisis of housing market in the U.S. which was another fuse to the world economic instability finds its origin, in the final analysis, to the "anti-terrorism war".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. administration has drastically cut down the social expenditures such as to health care and housing while increasing military expenditures without limits under the cloak of "anti-terrorism". It advertised a fine-sounding policy of tax reduction supposed to help people rise up for themselves by tax cut. But it was none other than the rich who benefited by it. Under the present U.S. administration, the number of the poor has increased some five million and the gap between the poor and the rich has got the broadest in history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The aggravation of the state in which the rich get richer and the poor get poorer resulting from the "anti-terrorism war" has inevitably touched off the crisis of real estate market and banking, while holding back economic growth by decreasing the expenses of the consumers, which is said to be the "motive power of the U.S. economy".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The crisis of the housing market is its concentric reflection. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is foreseen that the losses in financial sectors caused by the slumping housing market will continue growing. Coupled with the sharp rise of oil and protracted dullness in the auto industry, the stagnation crisis of the overall U.S. economy further come to the surface. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The United Nations Conference on Trade and Development in its report made public on January 9 warned the U.S. of pursuing a policy of sharp and disorderly dollar devaluation, noting that the housing market crisis and depression in the U.S. further increase the danger of leading the world economy to stagnation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, Board of Governors of the U.S. Federal Reserve System on Jan. 22 took one more measure of lowering the rate of interest to drive the world deeper into a commotion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the facts show that the politico-economic instability and mess in the world have been triggered off by the U.S. unlimited imperialistic rapacity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The progressive people across the world will vigorously turn out in the struggle for smashing the aggressive "anti-terrorism war" of the U.S. imperialists, the common enemy.

Message of Greetings to Indian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Saturday sent a message of greetings to Pratibha Patil, President of India, on the occasion of the day of the Republic of India. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The message expressed the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would steadily expand and develop in different fields in the mutual interests.

Russian Delegation Here  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- A delegation of "INTER RAO UES" Co. Ltd. of Russia arrived here today. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 During its visit the delegation is expected to discuss with the DPRK side the issue of cooperation in the field of power according to a protocol concluded at the fourth meeting of the Inter-governmental Committee for Cooperation in Trade, Economy, Science and Technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Both sides will focus on discussing the issue of supply of electricity to Khasan-Rajin railways and Rajin Port. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was greeted at the airport by an official concerned and a staff member of the Russian embassy here.

Reception Given at DPRK Embassy in Beijing 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Beijing, January 24 (KCNA) -- The DPRK embassy in Beijing gave a reception for officials of the International Liaison Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China on Jan. 24 on the occasion of the New Year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Jin Su, DPRK ambassador to China, speaking at the reception, said that the friendly and cooperative relations between the two parties and two countries have favorably developed last year under the care of the top leaders of the two countries and thanks to the common efforts of both sides. We will positively contribute to boosting the DPRK-China friendship in close cooperation with the International Liaison Department of the CPC Central Committee in the new year, too, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Liu Hongcai, deputy head of the International Liaison Department of the CPC Central Committee, said that last year the Korean people achieved new successes in different fields including economic development, overcoming natural disasters and the Sino-DPRK friendly and cooperative relations have steadily developed in depth. He expressed the belief that the friendly and cooperative relations will certainly be put on a higher stage under the deep care of the top leaders of the two countries and thanks to the common efforts of the Chinese and Korean peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK embassy gave a reception for officials of the Chinese Foreign Ministry on Jan. 22.

Indian Ambassador Hosts Reception  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 27 (KCNA) -- Indian Ambassador to the DPRK Zile Singh Saturday hosted a reception at the Taedonggang Club for the Diplomatic Corps on the Day of the Republic of India. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Kim Pyong Phal, chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea who is chairman of the Korea-India Friendship Association, Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Jon Yong Jin, vice-chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries, officials concerned and diplomatic envoys of various countries and representatives of international organizations here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there.

City Government of Ecuador Decides to Award Title of Honorary Citizen to Three Generals of Mt. Paektu  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- The Atuntaqui City Government of the Imbabura Province of Ecuador decided to present the key of the city to Kim Jong Il and the title of honorary citizen to the three generals of Mt. Paektu on the Day of the Sun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A special meeting of the city government was held in Atuntaqui City on Jan. 17 to decide to present its key to Kim Jong Il and the title of honorary citizen to the three generals of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A resolution was adopted at the meeting to award the title of honorary citizen to the three generals of Mt. Paektu and the key of the city to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The resolution noted that the city has the honor of presenting the title of honorary citizen of Atuntaqui City of Ecuador to President Kim Il Sung, Kim Jong Il and anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk and its key to Kim Jong Il.

Gifts and Congratulatory Message to Kim Jong Il from Russian Organization and Figures 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 27 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the State Academic Moiseyev Dance Company of Russia and a gift and a congratulatory message offered by its Director Elena Scherbakova and her husband and its leading members Marnopolskaya and her husband and Aristova in their joint name on the occasion of the February holiday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gifts and congratulatory message were conveyed to an official of the DPRK embassy in Moscow on Jan. 23.

Poster Exhibition Opens
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- A poster exhibition was opened at the Pyongyang International Cultural Centre on Jan. 25 to thoroughly implement the militant tasks set forth in the joint New Year editorial. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Displayed in the venue of the exhibition are at least 60 posters produced by the Mansudae Art Studio, the Central Fine Art Studio, the Fine Art Studio of the Ministry of Railways and Pyongyang University of Fine Arts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The posters fully reflect the idea and spirit of the joint editorial and the steadfast faith and spirit of the army and people to glorify this year as a year of gigantic struggle, a year of jubilation in the national history, when a great change will be brought about in the history of the country and the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Poster "Let's fling open the gate to a great prosperous powerful nation!" and others truthfully represent the steadfast determination and will of the Workers' Party of Korea to realize the grand plan and goal for the building of a rich and powerful country without fail in the near future with the might of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the posters are "Today's general advance means a general advance in ideology!" "Let's defend the headquarters of the revolution at the cost of our lives!", "Main front is economic front" and "People's-living-first" reflecting the militant spirit and enthusiasm of the entire army and all the people to give fuller play to the political and ideological might of Songun Korea in the general advance for this year, steadily augment the military power and build an economic power.

Rodong Sinmun Calls for Vigorous Movement for National Reunification
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- All Koreans in the north and the south and abroad should conduct a vigorous movement for national reunification to bring earlier the dawn of reunification, holding aloft the banner of "By our nation itself".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun today says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality more urgently requires the Koreans to intensify the movement for national reunification by their concerted efforts as clarified in the Oct. 4 declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is prerequisite to terminating the tragedy of national division as early as possible and achieving the national reunification to wage a vigorous movement for national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Neither difficulties nor obstacles lying in the way of reunification are insurmountable if the Koreans at home and abroad turn out as one in the above-said movement with patriotic zeal and fighting spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For the divided Korean nation to wage a dynamic movement for national reunification is the only way of carving out a rosy future of national prosperity.  It is an urgent requirement of the June 15 era of reunification to steadily develop the above-said movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The October 4 Declaration for Development of North-South Relations and Peace and Prosperity is exciting all Koreans in the north and the south and overseas and encouraging them to promote the patriotic cause of reunification with strong national self-esteem as it represents the desire of all the fellow countrymen for independent reunification and peace and prosperity and the need of the June 15 era of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a sacred national duty of the present generation to steadily escalate the above-mentioned movement. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Koreans fail to achieve the reunification of the country in the present generation, the task will be devolved upon the generations to come. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the divided country is handed down to posterity, this will bring most unbearable national shame to the present generation and amount to committing an indelible crime against the generations to come. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Whoever has the blood and soul of a Korean should come out in the reunification movement to have the country reunified in the present generation.

Building of Peace Mechanism on Korean Peninsula Called for 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- A prerequisite to defusing tension and removing the danger of war on the Korean Peninsula is to replace the armistice agreement with a peace accord, says Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To build a new peace mechanism on the peninsula is prerequisite to easing tension and removing the danger of war on the peninsula because there is no justification for the present armistice agreement to exist any longer, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To ease the military tension and ensure peace on the peninsula is an urgent issue which brooks no further delay in view of the trend of the times and the requirement of the prevailing situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean Peninsula is the only region in the world which has been in the state of truce and technically at war for more than five decades. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is urgent to replace the armistice agreement with a peace accord because the armistice agreement exists in name only due to the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It would be no more than an armchair argument to talk about the observance of the armistice agreement that has been reduced to a dead document due to the U.S. perfidious act. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The replacement of the armistice agreement by a peace accord would help defuse the military confrontation on the peninsula and smoothly solve the issue of building confidence between the DPRK and the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
There will be neither reason nor condition for the U.S. to refuse to opt for concluding a peace accord to replace the armistice agreement if it is truly willing to build confidence with the DPRK and co-exist with it in peace and stands for peace on the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The earlier conclusion of the peace accord would help convert the acute belligerent relations between the DPRK and the U.S. to those of peace and confidence and ensure lasting peace and stability on the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should face up to the trend of history and the development of the situation and take a bold decision to replace the armistice agreement with a peace accord as early as possible.

Judgment of Acquittal of Media Man Demanded in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 27 (KCNA) -- The People's Solidarity for Abolition of the "National Security Law (NSL)" of south Korea reportedly issued a statement on Jan. 23 denouncing the prosecution authorities for deciding to confiscate the works and photos made by photographer-writer Ri Si U seized by them after demanding 10 years in jail and 10 years of suspension of qualification for him on the charge of violation of the NSL on Jan. 10. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Accusing the security authorities of suppressing Ri on groundless charges of violation of the "provision calling for the protection of military secrets" in the NSL though he conducted legitimate academic activities aimed at exposing U.S. forces' bases for aggression, the statement noted that their action only revealed their ignorance. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The NSL is the main source of all the tragedies in which many figures of conscience are suppressed, the statement said, adding that such barbarous actions will never cease as long as there remains the evil law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement held that the NSL should be abolished as early as possible and tragedies in which the freedom of expression, artistic activities, thinking and scientific pursuit is being suppressed by the evil law should not be allowed to go on, as required by the trend of the times when inter-Korean reconciliation and cooperation are brisk and the overwhelming majority of the people are aspiring after peace and reunification after the adoption of the October 4 declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Underscoring the need to sternly judge the anachronistic acts of the security authorities and set right the judicial justice on this land, the statement strongly demanded the judgment of acquittal of Ri Si U and return of the confiscated works and photos.

Move to Pass "Motion Calling for Ratification of FTA" Assailed in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- The Headquarters of the All-People Movement for Checking South Korea-U.S. Free Trade Agreement in south Korea reportedly called a press conference in Seoul on Jan. 21 denouncing the move to pass the "motion calling for the ratification of the FTA" at the �hNational Assembly".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A press release read out at the press conference referred to the fact that even the political circle and big businessmen of south Korea have recently called for the early handling of the above-said motion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The NA should lend an ear to the voices of the people opposing the passage of the motion and the import of American beef, it said, warning that the lawmakers and political parties going against the people's mindset will certainly face a stern judgment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It urged the Unification, Foreign Affairs and Trade Committee of the NA to stop the move for the passage of the motion and start its verification, to begin with.

Dynamic Struggle for National Reunification Called for in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- The press headquarters of the South Side Committee for Implementing the June 15 Joint Declaration held a joint meeting on Jan. 21 at which it called upon media persons to turn out in the struggle to achieve the reunification of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers said at the meeting that the love for the nation is an important requirement for achieving the reunification of the country. They called upon all the media persons to come out in the struggle to realize the cherished desire of the nation irrespective of idea and ism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They stressed that the press headquarters, guided by the faith and will for reunification, would boost the exchange and cooperation with media persons in the south and the north on the basis of the achievements and experience already gained and thus make positive contributions to realizing the reunification of the country.

Information Bulletin Issued by CILRECO
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- The International Liaison Committee for Reunification and Peace in Korea (CILRECO) issued an information bulletin on Jan. 17. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin dealt with the background against which the concrete wall was built in the area south of the Military Demarcation Line on the Korean Peninsula and its scale. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin said that the existence of the concrete wall, the leftover of the era of confrontation, is an anachronistic one as it runs counter to the efforts for reconciliation, cooperation and reunification between the north and the south of Korea and establishing durable peace on the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It explained the just stand of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea on the nuclear issue on the peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin condemned the Japanese reactionaries for steadily intensifying the suppression of Koreans in Japan and the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The committee calls on all democratic organizations and human rights bodies of the world to denounce the Japanese authorities' crackdown upon Chongryon and demand its immediate halt.

Kim Jong Il's Feats Praised 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 27 (KCNA) -- The Korean Friendship Association Headquartered in Spain posted an article praising the undying feats of Kim Jong Il on its Internet homepage on the occasion of his birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The homepage in an article said that when progressive humankind found itself in ideological confusion, vacillation and pessimism due to the collapse of socialism in East European countries at the end of the 20th century, it was Kim Jong Il who tided over the crisis of the world socialist cause. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It recalled that he published "The Historical Lesson in Building Socialism and the General Line of Our Party," "Socialism Is a Science" and other famous works one after another, clarifying the main cause of the collapse of socialism in various countries, the lesson drawn from it, the sure victory of socialism and the way to be followed by the movement for rebuilding socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The publication of the Pyongyang Declaration "Let us defend and advance the cause of socialism" on April 20, 1992 provided an occasion of placing the world's socialist movement on the orbit of new upswing and the DPRK has become a beacon of hope and a symbol of conviction for the progressive humankind aspiring after socialism, it added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No force on earth can bring down socialism which the people absolutely trust and uphold, it said, stressing that socialism is sure to triumph.

DPRK's Joint New Year Editorial Supported in Russia
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- The Russian Association for Friendship and Cultural Cooperation with the DPRK released a statement on January 19 in support of the joint New Year editorial of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The joint editorial calls on all the Korean people to steadily strengthen the political and military might of Songun Korea and bring about a new leap in socialist construction and thus glorify this year as a year of the historical turn which will go down in the history of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international community supports the DPRK's stand to positively struggle for stability on the Korean Peninsula and world peace and further develop the friendly and cooperative relations with the countries friendly towards the DPRK under the banner of independence, peace and friendship in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement wholeheartedly hoped that the people of the DPRK would achieve greater success in building a great prosperous powerful nation true to the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il and thus glorify this year as a proud year of victory.

February 16 to Be Observed in Italy
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 26 (KCNA) -- An Italian preparatory committee was inaugurated with due ceremony in Rome on Jan. 18 to celebrate February 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 General Secretary of the Movement for Peace and Socialism of Italy Roberto Gabriele was elected chairman of the preparatory committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preparatory committee decided to publish Kim Jong Il's famous work and organize various political events including seminar and briefing on his exploits on the occasion of the February holiday.

Kim Jong Il dirige planta avicola y la de cerdos, de Kanggye
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 26 de enero (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea y Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, dirigio sobre el terreno la planta avicola y la de cerdos, de Kanggye. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ante todo, el Dirigente hizo visita de orientacion a la Planta Avicola de Kanggye. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tras recorrer la sala de educacion en las reliquias historicas de la revolucion y la de estudio de las memorias del Presidente Kim Il Sung, recibio el parte de los funcionarios de la planta sobre los trabajos realizados despues de inaugurada y recorrio varios procesos de produccion haciendo conocimiento detallado de la produccion y de la administracion de la planta. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Se mostro muy satisfecho de que en el pasado los obreros, tecnicos y funcionarios de la planta convirtieron la planta en una granja que sirve a la vida del pueblo, al establecer un estricto sistema de cria cientifica y disponer de nuevos procesos de produccion, y evaluo de altos sus meritos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La Planta Avicola de Kanggye desempena un rol importante en la mejora de la vida alimentaria del pueblo, senalo el Dirigente e indico las tareas que se presentan ante ella. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Lo mas importante en la normalizacion de la produccion en un alto nivel es resolver satisfactoriamente el problema del pienso, dijo y subrayo la necesidad de preparar una firme base de pienso y de asegurar por propia cuenta el pienso de proteinas y otros nutritivos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para aumentar la produccion de carne y huevos en la planta, apunto, es preciso obtener las buenas variedades convenientes a las condiciones topograficas de nuestro pais mediante el establecimiento de un sistema cientifico de reproduccion de nuevas variedades, cientifizar la cria y el cuidado, mejorar la administracion tecnica y de instalaciones y elevar consecuentemente el nivel de capacidad tecnica de los productores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ademas, -continuo- es necesario prestar profunda atencion a la investigacion cientifica sobre la avicultura, disponer de suficientes instalaciones profilacticas y establecer estrictamente un riguroso sistema antiepidemico para no perder ni un gallo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Acto seguido, el Dirigente visito la Granja de Cerdos de Kanggye nuevamente construida. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tras escuchar las explicaciones ante el panorama de la granja, la recorrio enterandose en detalle del estado de su construccion y administracion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Expreso una gran satisfaccion de que la provincia de Jagang construyo magnificamente esta moderna granja de cerdos de gran capacitacion y aprecio altamente los meritos de los constructores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Como resultado de haberse construido en la provincia de Jagang esta moderna base ganadera, sera posible aumentar la produccion de carne, dijo y presento las tareas ante la granja. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para aumentar la produccion de carne en la planta es preciso establecer el sistema de gestion cientifica basado en la tecnologia moderna y, al mismo tiempo, tomar las medidas concretas para el aseguramiento de pienso, solucionar por propia cuenta el problema del pienso y registrar un nuevo viraje en la cria de cerdos, destaco. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al enterarse de que la provincia de Jagang disfruta de un gran beneficio por la normalizacion de la produccion en un alto nivel de las bases ganaderas construidas en varios lugares, el Dirigente subrayo la necesidad de poner de pleno manifiesto la potencialidad productiva de las plantas avicolas, de patos, de cerdos y de conejos ya construidas para asi asegurar una vida mas rica y culta a los habitantes provinciales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Le acompanaron el secretario responsable del Comite del PTC en la provincia de Jagang, Pak To Chun, y el secretario del Comite Central del PTC, Kim Ki Nam.

ATCC analiza la causa de inestabilidad de economia mundial
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 26 de enero (ATCC) -- La economia mundial va cayendo en el crisol de disturbio total. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En estos dias, la creciente incertidumbre por el estancamiento de negocios en Estados Unidos produce a escala mundial la caida en picada del valor de acciones y resuenan voces inquietas y preocupantes de una eventual crisis economica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Es una opinion generalizada que el factor principal de esa inestabilidad de la economia mundial reside en la subida brusca del precio de petroleo y en la crisis desatada en el mercado de viviendas de EE.UU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Pero, en el trasfondo de ella hay las secuelas negativas de la imprudente politica belicista de EE.UU. y de la "guerra antiterrorista" lanzada por este. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En el siglo 21, a tenor de la estrategia de "guerra antiterrorista" orientada a mantener su posicion de "unica superpotencia", EE.UU. desato 3 guerras desde la afgana hasta la de Libano que ejecuto a traves de sus titeres israelies. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esta ultima contienda belica termino con la derrota de EE.UU. e Israel y el primero esta empantanandose cada vez mas en las anteriores guerras afgana e iraqui. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El fracaso de la "cruzada antiterrorista" significaria el fin de los "tiempos de EE.UU.". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por esta razon, este imperio invierte fabulosos fondos en esas guerras estrategicas y trata de buscar la salida de la seria crisis financiera en el aumento de exportacion mediante la devaluacion del dolar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La administracion norteamericana, que habia cambiado su politica del dolar fuerte por la del dolar debil, rebajo constantemente en los ultimos 3 anos la tasa de interes de esta moneda. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por resultado, se incremento la exportacion de EE.UU. y su deficit presupuestario marco en el ano fiscal de 2007 una cifra mas baja que las registradas en el ultimo lustro. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A cambio, a principios de este ano el precio del petroleo en el mercado mundial supero 100 US$ por cada barril por encima de su valor real, lo cual resulta una seria amenaza no solo para los paises consumidores sino tambien para los productores. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La politica del dolar debil de la administracion norteamericana, con que ella trata de eliminar los efectos catastroficos de la "guerra antiterrorista" sobre la economia nacional, deviene el factor principal del alza del precio de petroleo, incomparablemente grave que los actos especulativos y el "desequilibro entre la demanda y la oferta" en el mercado del crudo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La crisis del mercado de viviendas, otro detonante de la inestabilidad de la economia mundial, tambien tiene su genesis en la "guerra antiterrorista".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Bajo el pretexto de "luchar contra el terrorismo", la administracion norteamericana aumento en gran medida los gastos militares a cambio de la reduccion considerable de los egresos para las ramas sociales como la salud publica y la vivienda. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aunque anuncio la edulcorada politica de reduccion de impuestos, segun la cual los habitantes pueden mejorar por si solos sus condiciones economicas, los beneficiarios reales de ella son unicamente las personas acaudaladas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante el mandato de la actual administracion norteamericana, se registro un incremento de aproximadamente 5 millones en la cifra de los pobres y las diferencias entre estos y los ricos se agrandaron mas que nunca. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La exacerbacion de la situacion de "los ricos se hacen cada vez mas ricos y los pobres se tornan cada vez mas pobres", generada por esa "guerra", traera inevitablemente la reduccion de los egresos de los consumidores conocidos como "fuerza motriz de la economia estadounidense".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  De esta manera, frena el crecimiento economico y busca una crisis en el mercado de bienes inmuebles y en los negocios bancarios. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Una muestra coherente de ello es la crisis del mercado de viviendas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Se preve que iran en aumento las perdidas de la rama financiera a causa de esa recesion en el mercado de viviendas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A esto se suman el alza del precio de petroleo y el estancamiento prolongado de la industria automovilistica, los cuales acentuan el aspecto paralizado de la economia estadounidense en su conjunto. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al publicar un informe el pasado dia 9, la Conferencia de la ONU sobre el Comercio y el Desarrollo dio una senal de alarma a EE.UU. en cuanto a la brusca y desordenada politica del dolar debil argumentando que debido a esa crisis de viviendas y recesion economica, la economia mundial corre cada vez mayor peligro del estancamiento. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Sin embargo, la Reserva Federal de EE.UU. anuncio el dia 22 otra medida para rebajar la tasa de interes del dolar, que intranquiliza mas a todo el mundo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Como muestran los hechos, la inestabilidad y disturbio economicos, que hoy sufre el mundo de modo sucesivo, se originan de la insaciable apetencia imperialista de EE.UU. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La humanidad progresista del mundo intensificara mas su lucha por frustrar esa agresiva "guerra antiterrorista" lanzada por el imperialismo norteamericano, enemigo comun.
